<font color="#FF0000">NOT MORE TALKING HEADS........</font><br>
<tt>Fri Jan 16  5:56:47 US/Eastern 1998
</tt><p>
If anyone wants to get at the raw truth about the Vietnam War, they have but to identify themselves, and ask. <br><br>
&quot;Talking heads&quot; are an insult. We are real, our words are real, our feelings are real, and the Vietnam War was real.<br><br>
It was like the &quot;Howdy Doody&quot; show. We had the talking heads of Kennedy, Johnson, Nixon, MacNamara, Fonda, the Senate and House of Representatives, Ho Chi Minh, mental mush Officer Corps on rotation from Stateside funny farms, and a cast of thousands of &quot;Protestors&quot;, all mounted on puppet bodies, dancing around a little stage. All the cameras had big lenses to make it look larger than life.<br><br>
Meanwhile, while the show was in progress, the rest of us got chewed up in the physical and mental meatgrinder of 'Nam.<br><br>
I would say that was pretty pathetic.<br><br>
Now someone wants more of the same?<br><br>
Here I am, 28 years later, in psychological shambles from it all, and someone comes flying in on a broom, with a request for more talking heads. It doesen't seem anyone is really listening yet!<br><br>
If someone is REALLY motivated to learn and help, start with the VA, reform their bizarre and insulting system that is invoked when you ask for their help, get the Vietnam Veterans the help they need, and then someone might really want to talk, and not rip someones head off in the process.<br><br>
Answer this, O Great Talking Heads, how do I get this stuff out of my head? How do I keep myself from falling apart? How do I stop having to work every minute to keep my head on straight? How do I stop having flashbacks? How do I recover self esteem? How do I have the so-called &quot;normal&quot; life?<br><br>
Silence as usual.<br><br>
&quot;Mita Wasecun He O Makiyaki&quot;<br><br>
That makes more sense. <br>
  
<p><code>-- art16@ix.netcom.com  (Arthur Varanelli) </code><p>


